The paper focuses on zero-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new approach to zero-shot learning that involves training a deep neural network to generate visual feature classifiers from semantic attributes, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of cross-entropy loss, which is a common loss function in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed approach on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
